a, then repeat blending <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b> , until a fine consistency is achieved. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter or ghee and cook <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add remaining 400 g of the coconut milk, water, stock paste, Kaffir lime leaves, fish sauce, lime juice and salt and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh noodles into it. Cover noodles with boiling water and set aside to cook."},{"content":"Add chicken to mixing bowl and cook <b>7 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add prawns and bok choy and cook <b>4-5 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>, or until prawns are cooked through. Carefully remove Kaffir lime leaves using a slotted spoon."},{"content":"Drain rice noodles through simmering basket and divide noodles evenly between 4 serving bowls. Pour laksa over the top."},{"content":"Garnish with bean sprouts, extra sliced chilli and extra coriander leaves before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To prepare coriander roots for use in the curry paste, remove all the fibrous small brown off-shoots from the main root by scraping with a teaspoon.","Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or the<em> Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Chicken stock paste recipe.","Shrimp paste, also known as belachan, can be found in the International aisle of most supermarkets or specialty Asian grocers."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","40m","4 portions"]}